### Task 2: Build the EC2 Compute Child Module

Located in `own-terra-child-module-details/ec2-own/`, this module dynamically queries AWS for the latest OS image, spins up an instance type, and enforces corporate tagging standards.

#### `data.tf`

Queries the AWS EC2 catalog to dynamically fetch the latest Ubuntu 22.04 LTS AMI ID maintained by Canonical.

```hcl
# Lookup the latest official Ubuntu 22.04 HVM SSD AMI
data "aws_ami" "own_ami_ubuntu_IND" {
  most_recent = true
  owners      = ["099720109477"] # Canonical's Official AWS Account ID

  filter {
    name   = "name"
    values = ["ubuntu/images/hvm-ssd/ubuntu-jammy-22.04-amd64-server-*"]
  }

  filter {
    name   = "virtualization-type"
    values = ["hvm"]
  }
}

```

#### `main.tf`

Contains the actual resource definition for the virtual machine along with input variables used for customization.

```hcl
# Provision the EC2 Instance using the fetched AMI and input variables
resource "aws_instance" "own_ec2" {
  ami           = data.aws_ami.own_ami_ubuntu_IND.id
  instance_type = var.insta_type

  # Applying standardized tagging for resource tracking and billing
  tags = {
    Name       = var.user_defind
    ManagedBy  = "Terraform"
    CreatedBy  = "Infrastructure-Team"
  }
}

# Variable Definitions for Compute Customization
variable "insta_type" {
  type    = string
  default = "t3.micro"
}

variable "user_defind" {
  type        = string
  default     = "terra-module-insta"
  description = "Name tag for the EC2 resource. Required for identifying ownership in the AWS Console."
}

```

