### Task 3: Build the S3 Storage Child Module

Located in `own-terra-child-module-details/s3-own/main.tf`. S3 bucket names must be globally unique across all of AWS. This module pairs a random string generator with an S3 resource to guarantee unique naming, then passes the resulting bucket name back up via an output block.

#### `main.tf`

```hcl
# Generate a cryptographically random hexadecimal string to ensure S3 name uniqueness
resource "random_id" "any-id" {
  byte_length = 6
}

# Provision the S3 bucket using the random hex suffix
resource "aws_s3_bucket" "own-bucket" {
  bucket = "my-terra-module-bucket-${random_id.any-id.hex}"
}

# Output block to expose the fully qualified bucket name to the root context
output "below_is_the_bucket_detail" {
  value       = aws_s3_bucket.own-bucket.bucket
  description = "The globally unique name generated for the deployed S3 bucket."
}

```
